# Prefer `undefined` over `null`

- Do not introduce `null` in new code. Use `undefined` to represent missing or optional values.
- When updating existing logic, replace `null` checks and returns with `undefined` unless interoperability requires otherwise.
- Functions and interfaces should return `Foo | undefined` instead of `Foo | null`.
